flowRoot.flowPara: This is the main page of the settings app. The most used settings from the status area are duplicated here with a gear icon below them that takes the user to another page for more controls.
More useful settings follow with direct control of their values.

Finally we have list items that invoke separate pages for groups of settings. A plug-in system is required in order for apps to be able to add their own settings applets. (For system wide settings. App settings are encouraged to stay inside the app.)
Toggles with setting gear below, that opens a page with more settings. These are the settings that our user survey found out to be more useful
See the selectRoller (https://github.com/qwazix/glacier-controls-spec/blob/master/selectRoller/selectRoller.pdf) for interaction guidelines
This should include an off setting, that will turn off the mobile radio altogether as per the survey result.
We should not disable timezone and time/date setting when automatic setting is enabled.
Most of the time you just want to set the date/time in a hurry before the auto system gets a chance to update but don't want to disable the automatic setting.
Now in most platforms you have to disable the auto setting, set the time and then re-enable it, which is a waste of clicks
When the user clicks on "Set Time/Date" we show the Timepicker control as specified in glacier-controls-spec/timepicker
Ntp server address and update frequency
When summer time is checked all the times in areas that have summer time on the map increase by one, for example Athens becomes UTC +3
